The department of public health plans to dispose of 26 bodies that have been lying at the Naivasha sub-county hospital mortuary for the last four months. The department has issued a 21-one day notice for the bodies to be claimed, failure to which they will be buried in a mass grave at the Naivasha public cemetery. ALSO READ:

How death turned into my business The notice was signed by Naivasha sub-county Public Health Officer Carolyn Vata. She said the mortuary could only hold 12 bodies at a time. Vata said majority of the bodies were brought in by the police from various stations in Naivasha, Narok and Kiambu, while some were those of patients abandoned in wards.